unittitle.value: Records of the Office of Institutional Research and Planning

abstract.label: Abstract
abstract.value: The Records of the Office of Institutional Research and Planning contains published survey studies, notes, summaries and memos produced between 1959 and 1975. These include materials on New York University's academic programming, faculty, facilities and students.

p.value:
Additionally, this collection is in 
                <extref ns2:href="http://www.nyu.edu/library/bobst/research/arch/instresplan.htm">
                    <archref> off-site storage</archref> </extref>.

Identification of item, date (if known); Records of the Office of Institutional Research and Planning, 1959-1975; RG 6.3; box number; folder number; New York University Archives , New York University Libraries.

bioghist.head: History of the Office of Institutional Research and Planning

p.value: In 1971 the Office of Research Services became the Office of Sponsored Programs. That year the Academic Affairs Office also changed names, becoming the Office of Academic Development. These offices retain these names at this writing.
The Office of Institutional Research and Planning also conducted surveys and studies of faculty morale on topics including university policies, procedures, salary and students.
